.TH GETARG 3F
.SH NAME
getarg \- return \s-1FORTRAN\s+1 command-line argument
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B "character\(**N c"
.B "integer i"
.P
.B "getarg(i, c)"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Getarg\^
returns the
.IR i -th
command-line argument of the current process. Thus, if a program were
invoked via
.P
.DS
	foo arg1 arg2 arg3
.DE
.P
.I getarg(2, c)
would return the string ``arg2'' in the character variable
.IR c .
.SH SEE ALSO
getopt(3C).
.\"	%W% of %G%
